Interface IJSONMapPreProcessor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface IJSONMapPreProcessor

    This interface is used to pre-process a given JSONMap instance before IJSONMapProcessor is called. Implementations can modify the given JSONMap, and/or indicate whether the given JSONMap should be further processed or not.

    Usually you will not implement this interface directly, but rather extend from either AbstractJSONMapEnrich or AbstractJSONMapFilter, depending on whether you want to either enrich or filter JSONMap instances.

    Author:
    Ruud Senden
